# Cursor Rules Generator

## Rule Creation Process
1. Determine the appropriate rule type based on the request
2. Check if an existing rule covers this topic in `.cursor/rules/`
3. Create or update the rule following the template below
4. Place in the correct location with proper naming

## Rule Types

| Type | description | globs | alwaysApply | Filename Suffix |
|------|-------------|-------|-------------|-----------------|
| Always | blank | blank | true | `-always.mdc` |
| Auto Attached | blank | glob pattern | false | `-auto.mdc` |
| Agent Requested | descriptive text | blank | false | `-agent.mdc` |
| Manual | blank | blank | false | `-manual.mdc` |

## Template

```mdc
---
description: ACTION when TRIGGER to OUTCOME (or blank for Always/Auto/Manual)
globs: pattern (or blank)
alwaysApply: true/false
---

# Rule Title

## Requirements
- Concise, actionable items the agent MUST follow
- Each requirement must be testable

## Examples
<example>
Valid pattern with brief explanation
</example>

<example type="invalid">
Invalid pattern with brief explanation
</example>
```

## Critical Rules
- NEVER use quotes around glob patterns
- NEVER group glob extensions with `{}`
- Glob patterns are comma-separated: `**/*.ts, **/*.tsx`
- Keep rules focused — one purpose per file
- Maximum ~50 lines per rule body (excluding examples)
- Always include both valid and invalid examples
- After creation respond with: `✅ Rule created: path/rule-name.mdc | Type: {type}`
